| Feature / Storage Class     | `auto`                 | `register`                 | `static`                 | `extern`              |
| --------------------------- | ---------------------- | -------------------------- | ----------------------   | --------------------- |
| **Scope**                   | Local (block)          | Local (block)              | Local / File             | Global (across files) |
| **Lifetime**                | Function execution     | Function execution         | Entire program           | Entire program        |
| **Default Value**           | Garbage                | Garbage                    | 0                        | 0                     |
| **Memory Location**         | Stack                  | CPU Register (if possible) | Data segment             | Data segment          |
| **Value Preserved**         | ❌ No                 | ❌ No                      | ✅ Yes                  | ✅ Yes                |
| **Accessible Across Files** | ❌ No                 | ❌ No                      | ❌ No (file scope only) | ✅ Yes                |
| **Memory Allocation**       | Every function call    | Every function call        | Once                     | Once                  |
| **Keyword Required**        | Optional               | Optional                   | Required                 | Required              |
| **Typical Use Case**        | Normal local variables | Fast access variables      | Preserve state           | Share global data     |



auto is the default storage class for local variables.

register requests faster access but may be ignored by the compiler.

static keeps the variable alive for the entire program.

extern is used to share global variables between files.
